PHONE_REDACTEDT05:PORT:PORT.159828Z	   10 Query	insert into daily_analysis_reports (analysis_confidence,analysis_scope_note,day,executive_summary,generated_at,misconfiguration_signals,system_behavior_analysis,user_behavior_analysis) values ('The analysis confidence is high due to the large volume of data and consistent patterns observed across user activity, system behavior, and failure reasons.','This analysis covers a single calendar day (IST) on March 23, 2026, focusing solely on backend lead submission behavior.','PHONE_REDACTED','On the analyzed day (PHONE_REDACTED), a total of 190 lead submissions were made, with 142 successful and 48 failed submissions, resulting in a success ratio of 74.74%. User activity was concentrated among EMAIL_REDACTED and EMAIL_REDACTED, with the majority of attempts coming from the website_form.','PHONE_REDACTED:PORT:PORT.147729','An unusually high number of duplicate lead submissions (38) suggests potential configuration issues with the lead submission process or duplicate detection mechanisms.','The system processed 190 lead submissions during the analyzed day, with a maximum of 19 attempts per minute recorded and no burst minutes observed.','The users with the highest volume of activity were EMAIL_REDACTED and EMAIL_REDACTED, who accounted for a combined total of 290 attempts (86 and 104 respectively), 48 of which resulted in failures. The failure ratio for both users was similar, at around 25%.')
